accessibility_caption: Photo by Marco de Groot • Utrecht in Depot Boijmans van Beuningen with @archdaily, @archilovers, @mvrdv, @visitnetherlands, @designboom, @heijmansnl, @architecture_hunter, @boijmans, @rotterdam_info, @designmilktravels, and @glassarchitecture. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
This weekend the Depot @boijmans will open to the public! 🥳 ⠀
⠀
🌎 the world's first public accessible art depot holding over 151.000 artworks is a mix of an attraction and museum,  while not a museum 🤔 you know what I mean?🤷🏻‍♂️😂⠀
⠀
💡 what started as a crazy and unrealistic idea in 2004 is now a tribute to the many people who believed in this idea and made it come true 🙏🏻⠀
⠀
ℹ it starts at a diameter of 40m at the ground floor, slightly increasing with every level.⠀
⠀
Designed by @mvrdv who even updated their profile image for this occasion 😁🙌⠀
⠀
